  <content:encoded xmlns:content="http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/"><![CDATA[So now I've started tracking referrers. I'm using the referrer server variable, and running into canonicalization issues. For example, as I write this entry, there are 8 referrals from <a href="http://aspnetweblog.com">ASP.NET Weblog</a>. But it shows up on my list as 3 separate referrers since I'm not sure how to canonicalize the URL. For example, <a href="http://radio.userland.com/">Radio</a> users mostly come from the Radio.Weblogs.com server, so for those users, the specific virtual folder is important. But for other sites, like aspnetweblog.com, it's not. Anyone have a good suggestion?]]></content:encoded>
